NAME
       man - read manual pages bundled with Cervus

SYNOPSIS
       man [SECTION] PAGE
       man -l

DESCRIPTION
       Looks up PAGE in the on-disk manual under /usr/share/man and renders
       it to the terminal. If SECTION is given it is used directly,
       otherwise the search order is 1, 2, 3.

       Section 1 documents user-facing commands; section 2 documents
       Cervus system calls reachable via the libcervus bindings; section 3
       documents library functions exported by libcervus.

OPTIONS
       -l, -a, --list
              List every page found in the manual paths.

EXAMPLES
       man find
       man 2 read
       man 3 regex

FILES
       /usr/share/man/man1/*.1     command pages
       /usr/share/man/man2/*.2     system call pages
       /usr/share/man/man3/*.3     library function pages

SEE ALSO
       sysmon(1), find(1), grep(1)
